headline: Huntington Bank CFO talks Q3 results and regional bank loans
summary: Huntington Bancshares (HBAN) topped its third quarter earnings estimates, a quarterly release that coincides with Wall Street's newfound concerns for the regional bank sector over fraudulent loans. Huntington Bank Chief Financial Officer Zachary Wasserman speaks with Josh Lipton about the regional bank's latest earnings print and these credit risks materializing in the space. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination.

headline: How regional bank earnings helped put bank stocks back on track
summary: Big Banks kicked off the third quarter earnings cycle earlier this week, followed by other banking names like Bank of New York Mellon (BK), Charles Schwab (SCHW), and US Bancorp (USB). Meanwhile, Friday's batch of bank earnings from regional names like Truist (TFC), Fifth Third (FITB), Huntington (HBAN), Ally Financial (ALLY), and more helped ease Wall Street's credit fears that had sparked on Thursday. Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter David Hollerith joins Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton to outline the details. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Wall Street steadies after its slide as banks recover some of their losses
summary: The U.S. stock market seems to be steadying on Friday, as banks recover some of their sharp losses from the day before.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 198 points, or 0.4%, as of 12:49 p.m. Eastern time, and the Nasdaq composite was 0.3% higher.  All three indexes drifted between gains and losses through the morning, but the moves weren't as jarring as the big hour-to-hour swings they had earlier in the week.
